The paper deals with a well-known result in computational geometry, the Ham-Sandwich theorem, and its extensions to linear subspaces and families of hyperplanes. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves topological results and their applications, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.MG (Mathematical Software). The paper also discusses center transversals, which are related to geometric topology, making cs.GT (Geometric Topology) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions a conjecture by Langerman, which could fall under cs.SG (Social and Information Networks).
